"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092220","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-28","<p>The Housing Ombudsman Service has consulted on its draft 2019-20 Business Plan and draft 2019-22 Corporate Plan. The Secretary of State is required to approve these prior to their publication. The plans are geared around the Housing Ombudsman Service dealing with complaints as effectively and swiftly as possible and supporting the local resolution of complaints. Targets for 2019/20 will be agreed between the Housing Ombudsman Service and Secretary of State for the publication of the new plans.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-03-28T12:58:12.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092220/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092220/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1092220/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-20","Housing Ombudsman Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether he has asked the Independent Housing Ombudsman to change the six month target for determining case complaints in 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Jim Fitzpatrick","Poplar and Limehouse","Jim Fitzpatrick","234649"
