"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091295","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-27","<p>The number of speciality general practitioner training places commissioned and filled in the last five years in England is attached.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2019-03-27T12:39:12.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091295/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091295/answer","PQ234234 table format.docx","PQ234234 table format.docx","PQ234234 attached data","PQ234234 attached data","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091295/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-19","General Practitioners: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many training places for general practice were (a) commissioned and (b) filled in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","234234"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091296","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-03-22","<p>Since the start of expanded Troubled Families Programme, over 529,000 children between 0-17 years have been supported by the Troubled Families programme.</p><p>We do not report this per year as families are not limited to how long they can spend on the programme and as a result, children may be on the programme in more than one year.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Age group</p></td><td><p>Number of individuals</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>0-4yrs</p></td><td><p>142,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5-9yrs</p></td><td><p>165,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10-14yrs</p></td><td><p>156,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>15-17yrs</p></td><td><p>66,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>0-17yrs</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>529,000</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Total number of individuals on TF programme: 864,205</p><p>Figures correct up to 2017.</p><p>Time-lags in the national evaluation data mean that the programme’s impact cannot be assessed in real time.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2019-03-22T14:34:11.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091296/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091296/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091296/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-03-19","Families: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, how many children have been supported through the Troubled Families programme in each year since that programme has been in operation; and what the ages of those children so supported were.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","234235"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091297","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2019-03-22","<p>I meet regularly with representatives from social enterprises, charities and the voluntary sector. A full list of meetings is published quarterly on:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications</a></p>","Eastleigh","Mims Davies",,"2019-03-22T11:26:17.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091297/answer","Biography information for Mims Davies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091297/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091297/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2019-03-19","Third Sector","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, how many meetings the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Sport and Civil Society has had with (a) social enterprises, (b) charities and (c) voluntary sector umbrella bodies since her appointment in November 2018.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","234236"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091298","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-03-22","<p>No additional engagement has been undertaken by NHS England to that outlined in the previous response.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2019-03-22T14:15:14.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091298/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091298/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091298/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-03-19","Tomography: Oxfordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, pursuant to the Answer of 15 March 2019 to Question 231557 on Tomography: Procurement, what additional engagement was undertaken by the NHS on the effect of the proposed privatisation of the PET-CT scan service in Oxford on the location of those services outside Oxford.","false","Biography information for Anneliese Dodds","Oxford East","Anneliese Dodds","234237"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091299","Department for Education","false","2019-03-22","<p>The department is committed to supporting children and young people with speech, language and communication needs, as set out in our response to the ‘Bercow: Ten Years On’ review on 23 October 2018. A downloadable copy of the government response can be found here: <a href="https://www.bercow10yearson.com/" target="_blank">https://www.bercow10yearson.com/</a>. The department continues to engage with a range of government departments to reinforce this commitment.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2019-03-22T14:03:21.373Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091299/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091299/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091299/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2019-03-19","Special Educational Needs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what discussion he has had with the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities, and Local Governments on the establishment of a cross-Government plan for supporting children with speech, learning, and communication needs.","false","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson","234159"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091300","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2019-03-27","<p>The Government has confirmed that it will introduce a deposit return scheme (DRS) for drinks containers in England, subject to consultation. The specific model, scope and scale of any scheme is being considered as part of this consultation, which is also being undertaken with the Welsh government and the Northern Ireland administration.</p><p> </p><p>As waste and recycling policy is a devolved matter, the devolved administrations can decide policy separately. The Government is therefore unable to specify how a DRS in Scotland should be implemented, nor at this point are we considering specifically a pilot scheme. However, ministers and officials have met to discuss progress and recognise the benefits of a coherent system across the UK. DRS in England could form part of a coherent system across the UK and we will continue to work closely with the devolved administrations on this policy area.</p><p> </p><p>The role of a Deposit Management Organisation in managing the operation of a DRS, including being responsible for the maintenance of Reverse Vending Machines, is currently being considered as part of our consultation. We will consider alternative approaches as part of our analysis of the consultation responses.</p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","234161 ; 234162","2019-03-27T17:58:10.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091300/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091300/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1091300/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2019-03-19","Beverage Containers: Recycling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to ensure an alignment of the (a) design and (b) implementation of deposit return schemes in England and Scotland.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","234160"
